{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix X2 Setup Request handling for unknown eNBs\n\n### Summary\nThe X2 Setup Request handler in the eNB X2AP module incorrectly rejected setup requests from previously unknown eNBs by returning -1 instead of creating a new eNB descriptor. This caused X2 interface establishment to fail when peer eNBs were not already present in the association lists.\n\nThe issue occurred when `x2ap_is_eNB_id_in_list()` and `x2ap_is_eNB_assoc_id_in_list()` both returned NULL, leading to the function immediately returning -1 without attempting to register the new eNB. This fix modifies the handler to properly allocate and initialize a new eNB descriptor in this scenario, similar to how it's handled in SCTP association indications.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/X2AP/x2ap_eNB_handler.c`: \n  - Added `#include <stdlib.h>` for `calloc`\n  - Modified `x2ap_eNB_handle_x2_setup_request` to allocate new eNB descriptor when both ID and assoc_id lookups fail\n  - Initialize new eNB descriptor with proper association ID, connection ID, and state\n  - Insert new descriptor into RB tree and update instance counters\n  - Removed redundant `instance_p` assignment\n"
}